properties.Name: RacialCategory
properties.Description:
Note:   There is considerable disagreement about ethnicity and race among professions and the public in general.    However, since many government and social programs and activities are defined in terms of race and ethnicity there is a need to put forward a basic definition that can be modified as needed and is based on commonly accepted definitions of race and ethnicity.   Consider the common phrase "the human race" vs. "the black race" and you can see the lack of precision involved in the common term.

Race commonly references a classification of physical and genetic traits that are perceived to be common amongst a group.     There may also be a relationship to ethnic groups associated with race.

Race is most often associated with a common ancestral geography ("black" or "Asian") or commonly predicated upon obvious physical characteristics such as skin color, body shapes and similar means of differentiation.

Ex:
-  Black
-  Asian
-  Latino 
-  Pacific Islander
-  White
-  Native American Indian
-  Arab    

Within these broad racial groups are many ethnic groups as well as ethnic groups that have developed over time based on new geography, language, customs etc. ("Japanese" vs. "Japanese American") with the above characteristics:

ASIAN
- Japanese
- Japanese American
- Vietnamese
- Chinese
- Chinese American
- Filipino
- Korean
- Korean American

WHITE 
- French European
- Italian
- Italian American

BLACK
- Black American
- Black Native African

ARAB
- Arab Kurd
- Arab Turk
